cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) tasks, specifically machine reading comprehension (MRC). 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as adversarial training (AT) is a machine learning technique used in the paper. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as MRC is a subfield of AI and the paper explores the effectiveness of AT in improving MRC. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses neural networks for MRC tasks. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as AT has been successfully applied in image classification tasks, and the paper explores the effectiveness of AT in NLP tasks.
